rrent key issues and new case studies to illustrate the reality of practice today . This book contributes to crucial debates about the knowledge and skills essential for work with children and with parents in the childcare, health, social care and educational children’s services.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aChildrenxServices forzGreat Britain. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Children's Studies.2bisacsh1 aFoley, Pam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFoley, Pam, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFrost, Nick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeverett, Stephen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRixon, Andy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRixon, Andy, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aStone, Bill, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2014z9783111196343oZDB-23-BUPP0 cprintz978144731379340uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/9781447342991?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447342991423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447342991/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-BUPPb2014